  "prompt": "What are the dangers of eating too much flax seed?",
  "response": "While flax seeds are nutritious, consuming too much can lead to several potential issues:\n\n1. Digestive problems\n- Bloating\n- Gas\n- Constipation or diarrhea\n- Stomach discomfort\n\n2. Potential medication interactions\n- Can interfere with blood-thinning medications\n- May affect absorption of some medicines\n\n3. Hormonal effects\n- Contains phytoestrogens that could disrupt hormone balance\n- May cause complications for people with hormone-sensitive conditions\n\n4. Choking hazard\n- Whole seeds can be difficult to digest\n- Can potentially cause choking if not properly ground\n\n5. Cyanide toxicity\n- Raw flax seeds contain small amounts of cyanogenic glycosides\n- Excessive consumption could lead to cyanide poisoning\n\n6. Allergic reactions\n- Some people might experience allergic responses\n\n7. Nutrient absorption issues\n- High fiber content can interfere with mineral absorption\n\nRecommended daily intake is typically 1-2 tablespoons of ground flax seeds. Always consult a healthcare professional before making significant dietary changes, especially if you have pre-existing health conditions.",
